Next January 8, from 9:00 a.m. to 1:30 p.m., you are scheduled to take
the exam in the S87 system.
This new schedule is the result of the cancellation of the exam on
December 22nd.
I am only notifying you of this date so that, please, do not schedule
maintenance activities that could affect the correct performance of the
exam on the 8th in the morning.
If you need information or clarifications, please do not hesitate to
contact me
BR
Katrin

Dear colleagues,

Dear Prof. Mihai,

Thank you for your request.

Do you mean your "MASTER" user for your corresponding system in SAP GUI?
The language can be chosen while you are logging in by writing (EN).

Or do you mean your "U-User" for accessing the UCC Portal? There is also
an option to choose between DE (German) and EN (English)

I have attached to this ticket two screenshots.

If none of them, could you please specify which user you are mentioning?

Kind Regards,

Dear Prof. Mihai,

English. You may see the proof attached.

Could you please logout and logon again and see if the EN version is
functioning?

Dear Mr. Molenda,

Thank you for your ticket.

There is a more lightweight way of changing the stock.

In Fiori, you can go to the app ‚ÄúPost Goods Receipt without Reference,‚Äù
and you can enter your material, plant, and storage location.

If this does not work, you can also go to the SAP GUI in the transaction
MIGO. You need to enter ‚ÄúGoods Receipt‚Äù and ‚ÄúOther‚Äù in the select fields
on the top left of the screen. After that, you need to enter 561 as the
movement type on the right side of the screen (see the attached
screenshot). And then enter your material below.

I hope this helps you. If you have further questions, do not hesitate to
contact us again.

Philipp Landler

Dear Mr. Esteves,

Thank you for your kind clarification!

- You can share the MASTER user password for your SAP S/4HANA client
with the new teacher, just as you have shared it with teachers in the
previous semester.

In case you need technical assistance with reset of the MASTER User
password, we will gladly support you.

In case you wish to also refresh your SAP S/4HANA client for the new
semester, you can schedule that in the Client Resets Tool by following
the path: SAP UCC TU Munich Portal (www.ucc.tum.de) -> Customer
Self-Service -> Client resets.
Please kindly bear in mind that a client refresh erases all changes and
previous student progress from your SAP S/4HANA client. After a client
reset, your SAP S/4HANA client will be in the same state as after the
original delivery.
After a client reset, you will need to reset the MASTER user password
for your SAP S/4HANA client. This can also be done in the Client Resets
Tool.

- You can create a new U-User (U2PT022???) for the SAP UCC TU Munich
Portal for the new lecturer by following the path:

SAP UCC TU Munich Portal (www.ucc.tum.de) -> Customer Self-Service -> My
data
In the "My data" tool, click on name of your institution -> All users ->
Register new User.
Please bear in mind that the password for the new U-User should be 8
symbols long.

In case you are experiencing technical issues with U-User creation,
please do not hesitate to contact us.

We hope this information is helpful to you in preparing the necessary
logins for the new teacher.

Dear Mr. Esteves,

Thank you for your quick feedback!

Regarding Fiori interface:
Could you please kindly attempt to log in to Fiori with a LEARN-### user
like LEARN-000 or another unused LEARN-### user?
In general, the MASTER user is meant for the administration of the SAP
S/4HANA client and the management/unlocking of the LEARN-### student
users, and the LEARN-### users are meant for the case studies.
Therefore, the interface might look different for a LEARN-### user in
terms of usability for teaching.
Please kindly bear in mind that you need to unlock any previously unused
LEARN-### user before its first login to the system. The lecturer notes
in the curricula should provide you with instructions on LEARN-### user
management.

Regarding client reset:
In case you haven't requested a client reset until now, all the progress
of last years LEARN-### users / students is present on your SAP S/4HANA
client.
You have 1000 LEARN-### users (from LEARN-000 to LEARN-999) on your SAP
S/4HANA client. In case enough of them are still unused and available
for the students in your new curricular unit, you can continue teaching
without a client reset.
In case you wish to erase any progress from the last year's curricular
unit, or in case you do not have enough unused LEARN-### users available
for today's students, you should schedule a client reset.

Should you have any further questions, please do not hesitate to contact
us.

Kind regards
Alexandra Savova
SAP UCC Support

Dear ACC Team,

is seems like LEARN-015 locked the entries themselves. This can happen
sometimes when a Fiori Session is not terminated properly, and the
database locks persist.

The advised procedure is that LEARN-015 needs to log off the system
completely. After that, you or the lecturer can access the transaction
SM12, display all locks of LEARN-015, and delete them. Now the user
LEARN-015 can log in back to the system and the error should be able to
continue with the case study.

If there are further questions, let me know.

Kind regards
Philipp

Dear Gerhard,

Thank you for your ticket.

Archiving master data is only possible when no transactional data for it
and associated entries exist. Generally, marking master data for
archiving and archiving master data are complicated processes.

With your master user, you have the necessary roles to mark master data
for archiving. For Business Partners, that would be the transaction
BUPA_PRE_DA for marking the BP for deletion, followed by the transaction
SARA for archiving the BP. For more information, refer to the following
SAP Note: https://me.sap.com/notes/2640553/E.

If there is no urgent reason for deleting the master data, we do not
recommend doing it concerning the considerable effort associated with
it.

I hope this helps you.

Kind regards
Philipp

Dear Philipp,

Thank you very much for your prompt response! It seems to be a process
not worth the effort. I advised the student to keep track of which
customer master he keeps using, and ignore the ones excess to
requirements.

Dear Francisco,

Thank you very much for your feedback and for providing the screenshots.
We were able to investigate the issue. The error context was very
informative.

The link to S12 you used is correct.

The issue is caused by the following limitations in browser
functionality, related to cookies.

Firstly, in the normal browser mode, the login information for LEARN-000
is saved for system S12, client 323 in the memory/cookies of your
browser. Therefore, the browser always redirects and attempts to login
with LEARN-000.
Therefore, when you wish to login with any other user to system S12,
client 323, it is always better to use incognito mode.
Alternatively, you could try logging out of your SAP Fiori sessions
(Click on the circle with the user initial (M for MASTER or MAST
= ER-ESTEV) in Fiori on the upper right corner -> Log out) instead of closing the browser tabs.

We thoroughly tested login to MASTER and MASTER-ESTEV with incognito
Mode of MS Edge and Chrome. Here are our detailed best practise
suggestions which have proved successful in multiple login tests.

1) Use incognito mode
2) Login with one user to system S12, client 323 per active browser
incognito mode session.

The reason for this is that your first login to system S12, client 323
is also saved into the memory of the incognito browser. This memory is
shared across all open incognito windows and tabs. Therefore you can
login with one user to SAP Fiori per incognito browser session.
So, if you wish to login with MASTER and MASTER-ESTEV (or any other
user) simultaneously, please use two different browsers (i.e. MS Edge
and Chrome) in incognito mode.

Additionally, should you wish to log out of SAP Fiori in incognito
browser session, you can:
- Log out manually from all SAP Fiori windows (Click on the circle with
the user initial (M for MASTER or MASTER-ESTEV) in Fiori on the upper
right corner -> Log out)
- Close the whole incognito browser session (all tabs and all windows)
This measures for logging out in incognito mode could be used to enable
logging in with a different user to SAP Fiori.

For testing purposes, we changed the MASTER and MASTER-ESTEV passwords.
To spare you the step of allocation of new passwords, this time we
deliver the users to you with productive passwords.
The system will not prompt you to change these passwords.

User: MASTER
Productive password: uccnew11
Please share the productive password with other lecturers.

User: MASTER-ESTEV
Productive Password: uccpass11

We hope this enables a smoother login and password sharing experience.

Kind regards
Alexandra Savova
SAP UCC Support Team Munich

Dear Francisco,

I think there are some misunderstandings about how the master user
functions.

We deliver the SAP client with one master user. This user can be used to
unlock the LEARN users and administrate the system. As this is one user,
it only has one password.

If you wish for multiple lecturers to unlock LEARN users, you either
need to share the password of the master user with all applicable
lecturers or create new individual users with the same rights as the
master user (As Alexandra said, these individual users will be deleted
on a client reset and need to be created new).

However, if you do not want to create individual users for all
lecturers, you must ensure that every lecturer has the correct password,
as the master user is locked when the wrong password is entered

other helpful stuff for the beginning. The next training in English will
be at the end of May. Participation in the training is free of charge.

Regarding the Global Bike Monitor: This is a tool you can use as a
teacher to track your students' progress. This is helpful because you
can see which step the students have already proceeded and which values
they added. You will find further information in the GBI material folder
under "99 Instructor Tools". There, you can see the file regarding
Lecture Apps. In the chapter "Use of the Global Bike Monitor," on page
16, you find an introduction to how to use it.

student needs to start at step 1.

institution's SAP-A or SAP-V can trigger a reset via customer
self-services in our portal.

However, as these are rather complex issues, this may take a while each
time.

institution will receive more details on the process soon.

Good afternoon,

I am writing again regarding the new version 4.2 of GBI. As I was
informed, the current version and the new one can coexist for 4 weeks.
That is to say, we can maintain the current client and the new one for 4
weeks. I understand that during this period, if I understood correctly,
we could create transport orders from the current version to the new
one, in order to transfer all the parameters from the current version to
the new one as much as possible.

My first question, will we have to do this ourselves? I understand that
we do, but I would like confirmation.

Now, my other question. I hope I explain myself well. We have two
clients, 319 and 350. Would it be possible for client 319 to coexist in
the current version with a new one in version 4.2 for 4 weeks, for
example starting on June 1st? And would it be possible to extend this
period to 8 weeks? We need to make sure that everything is correct in
the new version, as we have customized everything for a new GBI in
Spain, and this requires a lot of extra work, which we must perform in
addition to our work as teachers.

In addition to client 319 coexisting in the current system with the new
one, would it be possible to maintain the other client, 350, until
August 15th in the current version? We have students defending their
master's thesis in mid-September, work that they have already started in
this client 350, and to give them time to finish it, since if we change
versions, they will not be able to use anything they have already done.
Until August 15th would be enough for us, as then we would need to make
a mirror copy of what we have customized in the new system so that the
new students can start classes on September 1st.

If I am not explaining myself clearly, please let me know.

We need to clarify this before speaking with all the faculty and making
a decision.

Best regards,

Andrea
